---
// IP-A5 iteration 5.6 — pryzm.so root landing page.
//
// Until this file existed, the root route resolved to Starlight's
// content-collection landing (the "PRYZM Developer Docs" page) — that
// is the right page for `/docs` but NOT for the customer-facing apex.
// Adding `src/pages/index.astro` makes Astro pick the file-system route
// in preference to the integration-injected one.
//
// Source-of-truth alignment:
//   - Manifesto headline beats: docs/01-strategy/manifesto.md §1 + §2
//   - Brand voice: manifesto §5 (aspirational result, plain-spoken work,
//     curated about what we ship)
//   - Colours: PRYZM_TOKENS — inlined per ADR-052 §1.3
//
// Astro renders this at build time; zero client-side JS.
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>PRYZM — BIM, reborn for the browser</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="The browser-native BIM platform: real-time collaboration, AI-assisted design, contract-grade interoperability. Built for architects, engineers, and the teams that have to ship a building."
    />
    <meta property="og:title" content="PRYZM — BIM, reborn for the browser" />
    <meta
      property="og:description"
      content="Real-time collaboration. AI-assisted design. Contract-grade interoperability. Built for the teams that ship buildings."
    />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <style>
      :root {
        --pryzm-purple: #6600ff;
        --pryzm-purple-lighter: #8c4dff;
        --pryzm-ink: #0a0a0f;
        --pryzm-paper: #14141c;
        --pryzm-paper-elevated: #1c1c28;
        --pryzm-border: #2a2a36;
        --pryzm-text-primary: #f5f5fa;
        --pryzm-text-secondary: #a8a8b5;
        --pryzm-muted: #8a8a96;
      }
      * { box-sizing: border-box; }
      body {
        margin: 0; padding: 0;
        background: var(--pryzm-ink);
        color: var(--pryzm-text-primary);
        font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;
        line-height: 1.6;
        min-height: 100vh;
      }
      header.site-nav {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        padding: 1.25rem 2rem;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--pryzm-border);
      }
      .brand {
        font-weight: 800;
        letter-spacing: 0.12em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        font-size: 1.05rem;
        color: var(--pryzm-text-primary);
        text-decoration: none;
      }
      .brand-purple { color: var(--pryzm-purple-lighter); }
      nav.site-links {
        display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; align-items: center;
      }
      nav.site-links a {
        color: var(--pryzm-text-secondary);
        text-decoration: none;
        font-weight: 500;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        transition: color 0.15s;
      }
      nav.site-links a:hover,
      nav.site-links a:focus-visible {
        color: var(--pryzm-purple-lighter);
      }
      main {
        max-width: 1100px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 5rem 1.5rem 6rem;
      }
      section.hero {
        text-align: center;
        max-width: 760px;
        margin: 0 auto 5rem;
      }
      h1 {
        font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem);
        font-weight: 800;
        line-height: 1.05;
        letter-spacing: -0.03em;
        margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
      }
      h1 .accent { color: var(--pryzm-purple-lighter); }
      .lede {
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        color: var(--pryzm-text-secondary);
        margin: 0 0 2.5rem;
      }
      .cta-row {
        display: flex;
        gap: 1rem;
        justify-content: center;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
      }
      a.button {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 0.85rem 1.75rem;
        border-radius: 0.5rem;
        text-decoration: none;
        font-weight: 600;
        transition: background 0.15s, color 0.15s, border-color 0.15s;
        font-size: 1rem;
      }
      a.button.primary {
        background: var(--pryzm-purple);
        color: #fff;
      }
      a.button.primary:hover,
      a.button.primary:focus-visible {
        background: var(--pryzm-purple-lighter);
      }
      a.button.secondary {
        background: var(--pryzm-paper);
        color: var(--pryzm-text-primary);
        border: 1px solid var(--pryzm-border);
      }
      a.button.secondary:hover,
      a.button.secondary:focus-visible {
        border-color: var(--pryzm-purple-lighter);
        color: var(--pryzm-purple-lighter);
      }
      section.beats {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        gap: 1.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 5rem;
      }
      .beat {
        background: var(--pryzm-paper);
        border: 1px solid var(--pryzm-border);
        border-radius: 0.75rem;
        padding: 1.75rem;
      }
      .beat h3 {
        margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
        font-size: 1.15rem;
        color: var(--pryzm-purple-lighter);
        letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      }
      .beat p {
        margin: 0;
        color: var(--pryzm-text-secondary);
        font-size: 0.97rem;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }
      section.callout {
        background: var(--pryzm-paper-elevated);
        border: 1px solid var(--pryzm-border);
        border-radius: 0.85rem;
        padding: 2.5rem;
        text-align: center;
      }
      section.callout h2 {
        margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      }
      section.callout p {
        margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
        color: var(--pryzm-text-secondary);
        max-width: 580px;
        margin-left: auto;
        margin-right: auto;
      }
      footer.site-footer {
        border-top: 1px solid var(--pryzm-border);
        padding: 2.25rem 2rem;
        text-align: center;
        color: var(--pryzm-muted);
        font-size: 0.9rem;
      }
      footer.site-footer a {
        color: var(--pryzm-muted);
        text-decoration: none;
        margin: 0 0.65rem;
      }
      footer.site-footer a:hover,
      footer.site-footer a:focus-visible {
        color: var(--pryzm-purple-lighter);
      }
      section.stats {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
        gap: 1rem;
        margin-bottom: 4.5rem;
        text-align: center;
      }
      .stat {
        padding: 1.25rem 0.5rem;
        border: 1px solid var(--pryzm-border);
        border-radius: 0.6rem;
        background: var(--pryzm-paper);
      }
      .stat-num {
        display: block;
        font-size: 2.25rem;
        font-weight: 800;
        color: var(--pryzm-purple-lighter);
        letter-spacing: -0.03em;
        line-height: 1;
      }
      .stat-label {
        display: block;
        margin-top: 0.55rem;
        color: var(--pryzm-text-secondary);
        font-size: 0.88rem;
      }
      section.section-block {
        margin-bottom: 5rem;
      }
      section.section-block h2 {
        font-size: 1.65rem;
        margin: 0 0 1rem;
        letter-spacing: -0.015em;
      }
      section.section-block > p.section-lede {
        color: var(--pryzm-text-secondary);
        max-width: 720px;
        margin: 0 0 2rem;
        font-size: 1.02rem;
      }
      ul.capability-list {
        list-style: none;
        padding: 0;
        margin: 0;
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
        gap: 1rem;
      }
      ul.capability-list li {
        background: var(--pryzm-paper);
        border: 1px solid var(--pryzm-border);
        border-radius: 0.6rem;
        padding: 1.1rem 1.25rem;
        color: var(--pryzm-text-primary);
      }
      ul.capability-list .cap-icon {
        display: inline-block;
        margin-right: 0.6rem;
        color: var(--pryzm-purple-lighter);
        font-weight: 700;
      }
      ul.capability-list .cap-detail {
        display: block;
        margin-top: 0.35rem;
        color: var(--pryzm-text-secondary);
        font-size: 0.92rem;
      }
      table.interop {
        width: 100%;
        border-collapse: collapse;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        background: var(--pryzm-paper);
        border: 1px solid var(--pryzm-border);
        border-radius: 0.6rem;
        overflow: hidden;
      }
      table.interop th, table.interop td {
        padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
        text-align: left;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--pryzm-border);
      }
      table.interop thead th {
        background: var(--pryzm-paper-elevated);
        color: var(--pryzm-text-secondary);
        font-size: 0.82rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.05em;
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      table.interop tbody tr:last-child td {
        border-bottom: none;
      }
      table.interop td.status-yes {
        color: var(--pryzm-purple-lighter);
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      table.interop td.status-roadmap {
        color: var(--pryzm-muted);
      }
      .principles {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
        gap: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
        background: var(--pryzm-paper);
        border: 1px solid var(--pryzm-border);
        border-radius: 0.6rem;
        padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem;
        color: var(--pryzm-text-secondary);
        font-size: 0.95rem;
      }
      .principles strong {
        color: var(--pryzm-purple-lighter);
        font-weight: 700;
        margin-right: 0.4rem;
      }
      @media (max-width: 760px) {
        section.beats,
        section.stats,
        ul.capability-list,
        .principles {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
        header.site-nav {
          padding: 1rem;
        }
        nav.site-links {
          gap: 1rem;
        }
        nav.site-links a {
          font-size: 0.9rem;
        }
        main {
          padding: 3rem 1.25rem 4rem;
        }
        .stat-num {
          font-size: 1.85rem;
        }
        section.section-block h2 {
          font-size: 1.4rem;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="site-nav">
      <a class="brand" href="/">
        <span class="brand-purple">▲</span> PRYZM
      </a>
      <nav class="site-links" aria-label="Primary">
        <a href="/manifesto">Manifesto</a>
        <a href="/pricing">Pricing</a>
        <a href="/trust">Trust</a>
        <a href="/getting-started">Docs</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section class="hero">
        <h1>BIM, reborn for <span class="accent">the browser</span>.</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          Real-time collaboration. AI-assisted design. Contract-grade
          interoperability. Built for the teams that have to ship a building.
        </p>
        <div class="cta-row">
          <a class="button primary" href="/pricing">See pricing</a>
          <a class="button secondary" href="/manifesto">Why we exist</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="beats" aria-label="Why PRYZM">
        <article class="beat">
          <h3>Designed in your browser</h3>
          <p>
            No install. No "open the file lock". Open the project — see what
            your team sees, on whatever device is in front of you.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="beat">
          <h3>AI that helps, doesn't replace</h3>
          <p>
            Apartment layouts in seconds. Furniture, lighting, ceilings on the
            same workflow. Every AI step audit-trailed — you stay in control.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="beat">
          <h3>Built on the standards</h3>
          <p>
            IFC, BCF, Revit round-trip, DXF, Rhino. Your model belongs to
            you. Your team's choices belong to the team.
          </p>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="stats" aria-label="PRYZM by the numbers">
        <div class="stat"><span class="stat-num">79</span><span class="stat-label">core modules</span></div>
        <div class="stat"><span class="stat-num">47</span><span class="stat-label">element plugins</span></div>
        <div class="stat"><span class="stat-num">18</span><span class="stat-label">element types</span></div>
        <div class="stat"><span class="stat-num">21</span><span class="stat-label">CI quality gates</span></div>
      </section>

      <section class="section-block" aria-label="What you can build today">
        <h2>What you can build today</h2>
        <p class="section-lede">
          Walls, doors, windows, slabs, stairs, roofs, curtain walls, beams,
          columns, ceilings, lighting, plumbing, furniture, rooms — and an
          AI workflow that orchestrates them into a real apartment in seconds.
        </p>
        <ul class="capability-list">
          <li>
            <span class="cap-icon">▲</span><strong>AI apartment generator</strong>
            <span class="cap-detail">
              Describe the brief; the deterministic layout engine + program-rules
              pipeline plan rooms, doors, windows, walls, ceilings, lighting,
              and furniture — together — in one undoable step.
            </span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="cap-icon">▲</span><strong>Real-time multi-user CRDT</strong>
            <span class="cap-detail">
              Yjs-backed Y.Doc per project. Two architects edit the same wall
              concurrently — both edits keep, conflicts surface explicitly.
            </span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="cap-icon">▲</span><strong>Plan, section, elevation views</strong>
            <span class="cap-detail">
              Generated from a single 3D model. Edit anywhere, see the changes
              everywhere — including the sheet layout you publish to PDF.
            </span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="cap-icon">▲</span><strong>Family Creator (apha)</strong>
            <span class="cap-detail">
              2D sketcher → constraint solver → 3D extrude/sweep/loft/revolve.
              Author parametric families locally; publish to the marketplace
              with an Ed25519 signature.
            </span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="cap-icon">▲</span><strong>Audit-trailed AI provenance</strong>
            <span class="cap-detail">
              Every AI workflow writes an artefact: model, cost, tokens,
              timestamp, prompt hash. Right-click an element → see exactly
              which AI step produced it.
            </span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="cap-icon">▲</span><strong>Apartment cognition rules</strong>
            <span class="cap-detail">
              Daylight, sightline, circulation, kitchen-triangle, privacy —
              validators that catch geometry that a renderer can't see
              before furniture is ever placed.
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="section-block" aria-label="Interoperability">
        <h2>The interop matrix</h2>
        <p class="section-lede">
          Your model belongs in your toolchain. PRYZM speaks the file formats
          you already use, on the standards bodies you already trust.
        </p>
        <table class="interop">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Format</th><th>What it carries</th><th>Status</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><strong>IFC 4 / 4X3</strong></td><td>Full BIM model — geometry, properties, hierarchy</td><td class="status-yes">Read · Write · PSet 80%+</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>BCF 2.1 / 3.0</strong></td><td>Issues + viewpoints — federated clash workflow</td><td class="status-yes">Round-trip</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Revit</strong></td><td>Round-trip via IFC4X3 + Python adapter</td><td class="status-yes">MVP</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>DXF / DWG</strong></td><td>2D plans, sections, schedules</td><td class="status-yes">Import · Export</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Rhino / Grasshopper</strong></td><td>3DM geometry import + bridge</td><td class="status-yes">Read · Bridge alpha</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>PDF / PDF/A-3</strong></td><td>Vector sheet output for transmittals</td><td class="status-yes">MVP · A-3 next</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>COBie</strong></td><td>Asset register for handover</td><td class="status-roadmap">Phase C</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>IDS / ICDD / bSDD</strong></td><td>Standards-driven workflows</td><td class="status-roadmap">Phase D</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <section class="section-block" aria-label="How it's built">
        <h2>How it's built</h2>
        <p class="section-lede">
          PRYZM is a layered TypeScript application enforced by eight
          architectural invariants the CI pipeline checks on every PR.
        </p>
        <div class="principles">
          <div><strong>P1</strong> Single composition root</div>
          <div><strong>P2</strong> One THREE owner</div>
          <div><strong>P3</strong> One requestAnimationFrame</div>
          <div><strong>P4</strong> No window-as-any escape hatch</div>
          <div><strong>P5</strong> Pure Zod schemas, zero I/O</div>
          <div><strong>P6</strong> Commands are the only mutation path</div>
          <div><strong>P7</strong> Visibility intent ≠ UI state</div>
          <div><strong>P8</strong> Every exported function emits an OTel span</div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="callout">
        <h2>Where we are right now</h2>
        <p>
          PRYZM is in alpha. Apartment typology ships first; house and small
          office land in the next two quarters. Read the
          <a href="/manifesto" style="color: var(--pryzm-purple-lighter)">manifesto</a>
          to see what we're building toward, or open the
          <a href="/pricing" style="color: var(--pryzm-purple-lighter)">pricing</a>
          to see how the tiers scale with your team.
        </p>
        <div class="cta-row">
          <a class="button primary" href="/manifesto">Read the manifesto</a>
          <a class="button secondary" href="/trust">How we handle your data</a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="site-footer">
      <div>
        <a href="/manifesto">Manifesto</a> ·
        <a href="/pricing">Pricing</a> ·
        <a href="/trust">Trust</a> ·
        <a href="/getting-started">Developer docs</a>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-top: 0.85rem;">
        © PRYZM. Alpha — built in public.
      </div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
